description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Engagement and Involvement Lead&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;18 month Fixed-Term due to funding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a passionate, values-driven Engagement and Involvement Lead to join us at Imperial College Health Partners (ICHP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ICHP is a partnership organisation bringing together NHS providers of healthcare services, clinical commissioning groups and leading universities across North West London. We have been designated by NHS England as the Academic Health Science Network (AHSN) for North West London, and we are one of 15 AHSNs across England which make up The AHSN Network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At ICHP we believe that innovation can be a powerful trigger to create new ways of working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through working with world leading hospitals, community providers, commissioners and universities, we match health challenges with new innovations. This helps our partners provide the best possible health and care outcomes for North West London’s 2.3 million residents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our strategic priorities are to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovate and collaborate for a healthier population making a real measurable impact; and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diversify our customer base in order to broaden our income sources and work where we can have the largest impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our organisation has a range of talents and experiences, bringing knowledge, skills and experience to the way we connect with our stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At a time where collaboration and innovation are crucial to help meet some of healthcare’s most pressing challenges, there has never been a better time to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a passionate, values-driven Engagement and Involvement Lead to work at Imperial College Health Partners. This is an exciting opportunity to help develop and deliver a strategic approach to engagement and involvement for ICHP, working closely with colleagues from across the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need someone with high levels of confidence, aptitude and diplomacy as well as exceptional professional skills and expertise. The role spans both strategic development and operational delivery and you will excel in both.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will form part of the senior management of the communications and engagement team and will manage a middle grade staff member, inspiring them to be the best they can be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll support the Associate Director of Communications and Engagement to develop a comprehensive, strategic approach to engagement and involvement with patients and the public.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll advise the Associate Director and broader ICHP team on methods to enhance engagement, helping to build positive relationships with patient and public groups, including charities, third sector and advocacy groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will see oversee the day-to-day planning and delivery of a high quality engagement and involvement programme. This will include all or some of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and overseeing the delivery of engagement and involvement activities to support client-facing work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing strategic advice and counsel to the Associate Director, wider ICHP team and our members when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with other senior leads in the communications and engagement team to ensure an aligned approach to projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advising staff on how patient and public involvement can support their programmes and projects, working in partnership with professionals where needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overseeing effective engagement and relationship management with charities, advocacy groups, patient and public networks and PPI leads across NWL and London.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held in the week commencing 16 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Natalie Hudson. Associate Director of Communications and Engagement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;natalie.hudson@imperialcollegehealthpartners.com&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 07814439932&lt;/p&gt;
